=============================
ORM (Over Represented Motifs)
=============================
Version 2007.12
Matthieu Defrance <defrance@scmbb.ulb.ac.be>
BiGRe ULB Bruxelles
http://www.lifl.fr/~defrance/ORM


INTRODUCTION
============
  ORM is a command line software that searches for locally 
  overrepresented motifs in a set of DNA sequences.

ARCHIVE CONTENT
===============
  README:    this file
  orm.py:    find over-represented oligomer
  ORM.zlib:  library needed by orm.py and ormbg.py
  Example/:  test data files

REQUIREMENTS
============
  Python >= 2.3

INSTALLATION
============
  Unzip the archive

USAGE
=====
  Second, search for overreprented motifs in 1.fa given a markovian model
  $ orm.py -i 1.fa --sort +seq --max rank 3 --markov=2 -v 2 > outputfile
